Andrea Cagan is an American writer and biographer . Cagan is a best - selling author whose work focuses on topics that raise public awareness and social consciousness . She has edited , and collaborated on more than fifteen books , including biographies of Diana Ross , Grace Slick , Joan Lunden , and Prem Rawat . She has brought seven books to the best - seller lists , including three New York Times # 1 best sellers and one Los Angeles Times # 1 best seller . In the early 1970 's Cagan was cast in several movies , including Captain Milkshake , an anti - Vietnam War film made in 1969 , which saw a revival in 2003 . Up and Running : The Jami Goldman Story , Atria Books ( 2001 ) . 